  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dc5\u0db8\u0dd4 \u0daf\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dba \u0db1\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0db1 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0da7 \u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd3\u00a0\u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0 315-6",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka 315-6 at the end of the first day",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Sri Lankan team, which is playing its first innings in the second Test against Pakistan, managed to collect 315 runs for the loss of 6 wickets when the match ended on the first day.",
        "Captain Dimuth Karunaratne won the toss and batted first for Sri Lanka.",
        "Oshadha Fernando (50) and Dinesh Chandimal (80) scored half-centuries for Sri Lanka.",
        "Angelo Mathews, playing in his 100th Test, was dismissed for 42 runs. Captain Dimuth Karunaratne scored 40 runs and Nirosan Dickwella managed to score 42 runs from 43 balls."
      ],
